news.title: Nagpur civic body tells realtors to deploy sprinklers in 15 days, anti-smog infra in a month
news.para: NMC’s town planning department has asked developers and builders to procure anti-smog guns and install sprinklers.

news.title: Assam government launches single-window portal for 103 urban local bodies
news.para: People under 103 urban local bodies (ULBs) will now be able to avail the municipal service along with other departmental services through this portal.

news.title: Panvel: 10 squads posted to speed up property tax collection
news.para: The PCMC commissioner and administrator Ganesh Deshmukh has ordered the team to crack the whip on the defaulters so that development activities could be carried out with the recovery.

news.title: Over 300 housing board employees win battle with Telangana government over plots
news.para: ​The HC also quashed GO 32 which restrained genuine allottees as well as set aside the order of a single judge restricting the benefit to a select number.

news.title: Mumbai: Illegal cement plant on Juhu open plot 'choking' residents
news.para: BJP MLA Ameet Satam has written to Mhada vice-chairman Milind Borikar and demanded that the agency move the HC to initiate contempt of court proceedings against the builder for renting out the plot even after handing over paper possession to it.

news.title: China's Country Garden aims to have offshore debt restructuring plan by year end: Sources
news.para: Country Garden which missed a coupon payment in October triggering default terms, then aims to start formal negotiations with offshore bondholders by February or March next year.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC demolishes unauthorized areas in Atharva Landmark
news.para: Originally meant to be a fully residential building, the space saw commercial shops being constructed in the basement area spread across over 3,0000 sq feet.

news.title: M3M promoter challenges ED notice, files pre-arrest bail plea
news.para: After hearing arguments from the defense counsel and senior prosecutors of the ED, special PMLA judge Rajeev Goyal fixed November 17 as the next date of hearing for orders on the bail application.

news.title: Consumer commission issues arrest warrant against Supertech Realtors' director
news.para: The Consumer Dispute Redressal Commission, Ahmedabad (rural) has ordered Kalkaji police station in New Delhi to arrest the director of Supertech Realtors Pvt Ltd, Harish Chander Chhibber, and produce him before the commission on December 12.

news.title: Spain's Colonial posts $320 million loss for Jan-Sept 2023
news.para: Colonial Chief Executive Pere Vinolas said in a call with journalists that the asset revaluation process, which was weighing on property prices, was not over yet.

news.title: B.L. Kashyap & Sons posts net profit of Rs 11.99 crore in Q2 FY24
news.para: B.L. Kashyap & Sons' net consolidated total revenue stood at Rs 327.64 crore, a growth of 9.55 per cent from Rs 299.09 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: English tenants hit with most no-fault eviction claims since 2016
news.para: Between July and September, landlords in England started 8,399 no-fault eviction court proceedings against their tenants - the highest number since the second quarter of 2016, figures from the Ministry of Justice showed.

news.title: Vipul posts net loss of Rs 17.08 crore in Q2 FY24
news.para: Vipul's net consolidated total revenue stood at Rs 9.80 crore, a dip of 79.86 per cent from Rs 48.65 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Creditor asks landlord SBB for immediate repayment of loan
news.para: U.S hedge fund Fir Tree Partners told Reuters it was accelerating the notes and starting proceedings against SBB for recovery of the debt.

news.title: Ashiana Housing posts net profit of Rs 27.35 crore in Q2 FY24
news.para: Ashiana Housing's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 351.02 crore, a growth of 282.71 per cent from Rs 91.72 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Gurugram: Four balconies of Chintels Paradiso's Tower D collapse, no casualty
news.para: Later, Towers D, E, F, G, and H of the society located in sector 109 were declared unsafe for habitation in the structural audit report by the Indian Institute of Technology, Delhi. The society has nine towers in total.

news.title: Mahindra Lifespaces cancels joint development of 4.8-acre land in Mumbai's Dahisar
news.para: Mahindra Lifespaces also received a notice from Pimpri Chinchwad Municipal Corporation, imposing a penalty of Rs. 4.6 lakh for alleged non-adherence to applicable directions to combat air pollution in construction site.

news.title: Shriram Properties' net profit up 2.91% in Q2 FY24
news.para: Shriram Properties' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 231.24 crore, a dip of 16.17 per cent from Rs 275.83 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Kanpur development body to e-auction 608 plots
news.para: According to KDA PRO S B Rai, bidding for e-auction will take place between November 10 and December 10. The land, under planning area, has been covered by a boundary wall.
